{
  "slug": "mcp-server-dev",
  "name": "Mcp Server Dev",
  "type": "plugin",
  "description": "Skills for designing and building MCP servers that work seamlessly with Claude — guides you through deployment models (remote HTTP, MCPB, local), tool design patterns, auth, and interactive MCP apps.",
  "longDescription": "Ships **3 skills** covering different MCP development paths:\n\n- **build-mcp-server**: Remote Streamable-HTTP servers with references for auth (DCR/CIMD), tool design, Cloudflare Workers deployment, elicitation, resources, and prompts\n- **build-mcp-app**: Interactive UI widgets (forms, pickers, confirm dialogs) rendered inline in chat, with iframe sandbox and SDK message references\n- **build-mcpb**: Packaged local stdio servers with bundled runtimes so users skip Node/Python setup, with manifest schema and security references\n\nCovers TypeScript SDK (`@modelcontextprotocol/sdk`) and FastMCP 3.x (Python). Recommends one-per-action tool design under ~15 operations, search + execute pattern for larger APIs.",
